{
  "texts": [
    "The resequenced accessions displayed a geographic split along the Eastern versus Western sides of the Great Rift Valley, with cultivated coffee variants all placed with the Eastern population.",
    "Such admixture has played a large role in breeding many fruit-bearing crops, the nonpolyploid allogamous perennial lychee being one of the most extreme cases 58.",
    "The prevalent autogamy of Arabica, combined with the multiple genetic bottlenecks it underwent in the wild, may have selectively purged deleterious alleles, explaining the capacity of the species to survive single-plant bottlenecks that occurred during its cultivation.",
    "An additional element buffering deleterious alleles was probably Arabica's allopolyploidy itself, which provided some level of heterosis 77.",
    "However, the narrow genetic basis of both cultivated and wild modern Arabica constitutes a major drawback, as well as an obstacle for its breeding using wild genepool diversity."
  ]
}